<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Aug Strength</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Base strength = 168<br>
Base weapon skill = 979<br>
<br>
Aug1:<br>
Strength = 174 (+6)<br>
Weapon skill = 997 (+18)<br>
<br>
Aug2:<br>
Strength = 180 (+6)<br>
Weapon skill = 1016 (+19)<br>
<br>
Aug3:<br>
Strength = 186 (+6)<br>
Weapon skill = 1034 (+18)<br>
<br>
+ Ws from weapon =<br>
<br>
39+15 = 979 weapon skill<br>
39+14 = 969 weapon skill<br>
<br>
So each level of aug strength is equal to 1.8/1.9 points of weapon overcapping 50.<br>
<br>
------------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Aug con</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
At level 50 RR5 dwarf Skald has:<br>
<br>
Base constitution = 149<br>
Base hit points = 1352<br>
<br>
Aug1:<br>
Constitution = 155 (+6)<br>
Hit points = 1375 (+23)<br>
<br>
Aug2:<br>
Constitution = 161 (+6)<br>
Hit points = 1397 (+22)<br>
<br>
Aug3:<br>
Constitution = 167 (+6)<br>
Hit points = 1420 (+23)<br>
<br>
At level 25 a Norse Skald has:<br>
<br>
Base con = 77<br>
Base hit points = 448<br>
<br>
So <br>
448/77 = 5.8 hps per con<br>
thus<br>
5.8hps*6con = 34.9 hps<br>
<br>
however when I do aug con 1 I get:<br>
<br>
Aug con 1:<br>
Constitution = 83 (+6)<br>
Hit points = 460 (+12)<br>
<br>
Not 483 hit points (+35) as would be expected.<br>
<br>
Anyone know what the reason for this is? A cap for being lower than 50 or RR5 is the only reason I can see.  I was hopeing to find a direct link for 1 con = ## hps. <br>
